# Git Workflow Assistant

Help with Git operations following Cadre conventions.

## Branch Naming

Format: `{type}/{short-description}`

Types:
- `feat/` - New features
- `fix/` - Bug fixes
- `refactor/` - Code refactoring
- `docs/` - Documentation
- `test/` - Adding tests
- `chore/` - Maintenance

Examples:
- `feat/user-authentication`
- `fix/login-timeout`
- `refactor/api-client`

## Commit Messages

Format: `type(scope): short summary`

```
feat(auth): add OAuth2 login support
fix(api): handle null response from users endpoint
refactor(utils): extract validation helpers
docs(readme): update installation instructions
test(api): add integration tests for orders
```

## Common Operations

```bash
# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feat/feature-name

# Sync with main
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main

# Interactive rebase (clean history)
git rebase -i HEAD~3

# Squash merge to main
git checkout main
git merge --squash feat/feature-name
git commit -m "feat(scope): description"
```

## Best Practices

- Commit early and often
- Use `git pull --rebase`
- Squash merge to main
- Keep commits atomic
- Write descriptive messages
